
1. Linux & Darwin
-----------------

   $ ./libssh2-make-linux.sh
   $ cd src-linux
   $ ddk-build


2. Windows
----------

   $ ./libssh2-make-mingw.sh
   $ cd src-mingw
   $ ddk-build --add-target=mingw-linux-x86_64


3. Android
----------

   $ ./libssh2-make-linux.sh
   $ cd src-linux
   $ ddk-build --add-target=android-x86
   $ ddk-build --add-target=android-x86_64
   $ ddk-build --add-target=android-armv7
   $ ddk-build --add-target=android-arm64

   or

   $ ./build-libssh2-android.sh


4. IOS
------

   $ ./libssh2-make-linux.sh
   $ cd src-linux
   $ ddk-build --add-target=ios-x86
   $ ddk-build --add-target=ios-x86_64
   $ ddk-build --add-target=ios-armv7
   $ ddk-build --add-target=ios-armv7s
   $ ddk-build --add-target=ios-arm64

   or

   $ ./build-libssh2-ios.sh

   * ios/build-libssh2.sh: This is old method.

